<div class="clever-body">
  <div class="clever-grid-row">
    <div class="clever-grid-column-full">
      <h1 class="clever-heading-xl">Cookies</h1>

      <p>Candidate Bay puts small files (known as ‘cookies’) onto your computer to collect information about how you
        browse the site.</p>

      <p>Cookies are used to:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Identify your session with us, which means we have authenticated you</li>
        <li>measure how you use the website so it can be updated and improved based on your needs</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Find out more about <a href="https://ico.org.uk/your-data-matters/online/cookies/">how to manage cookies.</a>
        at the UK Information Commissioner's office</p>

      <h2>How cookies are used on the Candiate Bay</h2>

      <h3>Managing your access and experience</h3>

      <p>We use cookies to provide you with a better website experience, manage access/use of the system and provide you
        with features and functionality. For instance, we use cookies to ensure you’re accessing the system from a
        trusted computer, and that you see features and information relevant to you.</p>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_session</td>
          <td>We use this cookie to keep track of what we’ve shown you. It remembers your interactions, so you don’t
            have to repeat them.
          </td>
          <td>When you close your browser</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <h3>Measuring website usage (Google Analytics)</h3>

      <p>We use Google Analytics software to collect information about how you use Candiate Bay. We do this to help make
        sure the site is meeting the needs of its users and to help us make improvements, eg improving site search.</p>

      <p>Google Analytics stores information about:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>the pages you visit on Candidate Bay</li>
        <li>how long you spend on each page in our site</li>
        <li>how you got to the us</li>
        <li>what you click on while you’re visiting the site</li>
        <li>We don’t collect or store your personal information (eg your name or address) so this information can’t be
          used to identify who you are.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>We don’t allow Google to use or share our analytics data.</p>

      <p>Google Analytics sets the following cookies:</p>

      <h3>Universal Analytics</h3>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_ga</td>
          <td>This helps us count how many people visit Candiate Bay by tracking if you’ve visited before</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_gat</td>
          <td>Used to manage the rate at which page view requests are made</td>
          <td>10 minutes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_gid</td>
          <td>Used to understand how pages are linked together</td>
          <td>1 day</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <h3>Google Analytics</h3>

      <table>
        <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tr>
          <td>_utma</td>
          <td>Like _ga, this lets us know if you’ve visited before, so we can count how many of our visitors are new to
            Candiate Bay or to a certain page
          </td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_utmb</td>
          <td>This works with _utmc to calculate the average length of time you spend on Candiate Bay</td>
          <td>30 minutes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_utmc</td>
          <td>This works with _utmb to calculate when you close your browser</td>
          <td>when you close your browser</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_utmz</td>
          <td>This tells us how you reached Candiate Bay (eg from another website or a search engine)</td>
          <td>6 months</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <p>You can <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">opt-out of Google Analytics</a></p>

      <h3>Our introductory message</h3>

      <p>You may see a pop-up welcome message when you first visit Candiate Bay. We’ll store a cookie so that your
        computer knows you’ve seen it and knows not to show it again.</p>

      <table>
        <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tr>
          <td>seen_cookie_message</td>
          <td>Saves a message to let us know that you’ve seen our cookie message</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <h3>Other services</h3>
      <p>We aim to follow UK public-body guidelines for accessibility, readability, usability and also cookies.
        Thus:</p>
      <blockquote>This policy is for Candiate Bay only. When you go to a service run by a different organisation, they
        may have their own cookies policy.
      </blockquote>
